-- Tanzania Power Utility Suspends Officials Amid Investigation
-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 2012-07-16T11:34:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/tanzania-power-utility-suspends-officials-amid-investigation.html
The Tanzania Electric Supply Co.
suspended Managing Director William Mhando and three other
officers amid an investigation into embezzlement and abuse of
office, the government said.  The board decided on the suspensions on July 14, January
Makamba, deputy minister for communication, science and
technology, said in an e-mail from  Dar es Salaam , Tanzania’s
commercial hub.  Mhando didn’t answer two calls to his mobile phone today
seeking comment. The other officials suspended include the
deputy managing director for corporate services, a finance
officer and a procurement officer, according to Makamba.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Dar es Salaam via Nairobi at
   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 